Package: mqvpn
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 libmqvpn0 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Multipath QUIC VPN using MASQUE CONNECT-IP
 mqvpn is a VPN daemon implementing MASQUE CONNECT-IP (RFC 9484) over
 HTTP Datagrams and QUIC DATAGRAMs, with Multipath QUIC support for
 bandwidth aggregation and seamless failover across multiple interfaces.
 .
 Features:
  - Multipath (WiFi + LTE, dual ISP) with WLB scheduler
  - Standards-based: MASQUE CONNECT-IP (RFC 9484)
  - Dual-stack IPv4 + IPv6 inside the tunnel
  - PSK authentication and per-user credentials
  - DNS override to prevent leaks
  - Backup/failover paths (standby until all primary paths are down)
  - JSON control API for runtime management

Package: libmqvpn0
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Description: Multipath QUIC VPN shared library
 Shared library for embedding the mqvpn client engine in applications.
 Provides a sans-I/O API for use in custom event loops or on Android
 via JNI.

Package: libmqvpn-dev
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 libmqvpn0 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Multipath QUIC VPN development files
 Header and static library for building applications against libmqvpn.
